cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.MM 

This paper deals with object detection and adversarial attacks, which are commonly studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) communities. The paper also discusses the use of contextual reasoning in object detection, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The vulnerability of object detectors to adversarial attacks is a security concern, which is studied in the computer security (cs.CR) community. Finally, the paper presents a method for generating adversarial patches, which is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
